### 13.8 Debugging Checklist

**If segments are not being created:**
1. ✅ Check `full_description` is populated (not empty/null)
2. ✅ Verify timestamps exist in `full_description` using regex: `/\d{1,2}:\d{2}/`
3. ✅ Check Phase 1 keyword filter: Does text after timestamp contain "AIK"?
4. ✅ Verify Phase 2 AI validation triggers if Phase 1 = 0 matches
5. ✅ Check `keyword_timestamp_description` ≠ `video_title` (title fallback bug)

**If wrong number of segments created:**
```sql
-- Debug query: Count segments per video
SELECT 
  op.youtube_video_id,
  op.title,
  COUNT(vs.id) as segment_count,
  array_agg(vs.keyword_timestamp ORDER BY vs.keyword_timestamp_seconds) as timestamps
FROM public.youtube_videos_operational op
LEFT JOIN public.video_segments vs ON vs.operational_video_id = op.id
GROUP BY op.youtube_video_id, op.title
ORDER BY segment_count DESC;
```

**If deep links not working:**
```sql
-- Verify deep link format
SELECT 
  youtube_video_id,
  keyword_timestamp,
  keyword_timestamp_seconds,
  youtube_deep_link
FROM public.video_segments
WHERE youtube_deep_link NOT LIKE '%&t=%s';
-- Should return 0 rows (all deep links should have &t=XXXs format)
```

